Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @pecan nut halves{25}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{90}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the leek and a knob of @?butter{1%knob}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic, pecans and @dried rosemary{1}. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}, then transfer to a large #bowl{} and set aside to cool slightly.

While the leek cooks, trim the @brussels sprouts{200} and halve through the root.

Pop them onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer and set aside for now.

Cut the @puff pastry sheet{1} into equal-sized rectangles (2 per person).

Once the leeks have cooled slightly, add the @British pork and oregano sausage meat{225} and cheese to the bowl and mix together with your hands. Roll your sausage meat filling into even-sized balls, 2 per person.

Place a ball onto one half of each pastry rectangle, then flatten the filling out into a 1cm slab, leaving a 1cm border at the sides. Dampen the edges of the pastry with a little @water{}, then fold the top half of the pastry over the filling to enclose it.

Gently press the edges down with the back of a #fork{} to tightly seal the parcel on the 3 open sides.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Carefully transfer your empanadas to a lined baking tray. Using a #knife{}, make a small slit over the top of each to allow steam to escape.

Drizzle with @oil{} and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the pastry is golden and the filling is cooked, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The sausage meat is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, roast the sprouts on the top shelf until browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

When the sprouts have 10 mins left, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60} to the same tray and continue to cook for the remaining time until golden, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.

Once the sprouts and lardons are cooked, drizzle over the @redcurrant jelly{25} and toss to coat. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Share your Christmas stuffing inspired empanadas and roasted sprouts between your plates.

Serve the @baby leaf mix{50} alongside drizzled with the @balsamic glaze{12}.

Enjoy!